# Live /now dashboard sources. Copy to `.env.local` and fill in.
# Every var is optional — a tile without credentials renders a quiet
# "not connected yet" state instead of failing.

# --- Spotify (Listening tile) ---------------------------------------------
# Create an app at https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard, then run the
# Authorization Code flow once (scopes: user-read-currently-playing
# user-read-recently-played user-top-read) to obtain a long-lived refresh token.
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN=

# --- GitHub (Building tile) -----------------------------------------------
# Optional. Username is derived from the GitHub link in lib/site.ts; override
# here if needed. A token (classic, no scopes needed for public events) only
# raises the rate limit from 60 to 5000 req/hr.
GITHUB_USERNAME=
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# --- This site tile --------------------------------------------------------
# No configuration needed. Deploy info is read from Vercel's automatically
# exposed system env vars (VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_*) in production, and from local
# git in dev. The live response check needs no credentials.

# --- In SF tile ------------------------------------------------------------
# No configuration needed — weather + air quality come from Open-Meteo, which
# requires no API key.
